Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, trim the @Green Beans{80%g} and cut into thirds.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and green beans, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks.

Meanwhile, open the remaining sachets.

Drain the fat from the mince. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Peanut Butter{30%g}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g}, @Honey{15%g} and @Water{150%ml}(for the sauce) to the pan. Stir well.

Simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Share your rice between #bowls{}.

Top with the stir-fry.

Sprinkle over the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} to finish.

Enjoy!